text:
Cedar Grove Cemetery:

Horace Harding Boulevard (formerly Strongs Causeway), south side, at the N.W. corner of Cedar Grove Cemetery, showing in a set of four views the home of the former Lt. Gov. Cadwallader Colden in 1763. The house was demolished in October 1930. See other views for more data. See also Long Island History by Overton.

October 1924.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
